Presentation to the Max Planck Institute (2021)

The following graphics are a part of a presentation of the Legal Modernism project. Given by Kellen Funk, the presentation is titled The Making of Modern Law: Digital Computation and the Search for Anglo-American Legal Modernity. It will be given on 1 March 2021 at the Digital Methods and Resources in Legal History virtual symposium organized by the Max Planck Institute for Legal History and Legal Theory.

Citation data is drawn from the Caselaw Access Projects citation graph. Source code is available at the projects GitHub repository.
